This paper deals with data quality and dependency discovery, which are topics commonly studied in the database community (cs.DB). The use of dynamic programming and optimization techniques suggests a focus on algorithmic aspects, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses experimental evaluation, which is a common practice in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) as well as cryptography (cs.CR).
